log_monitor is a small/simple tool for monitoring log files, written in Python. It is designed to be used together with other job scheduler (eg: cron).

Main features:
- Monitor a set of text patterns that are defined by regex
- Block-wise text matching, a block can either be a single line or multiple lines
- Monitor the size and idle time of target file
- Send email notifications on detected events via SMTP
- Play sound on detected events (available only in Windows)

Sample usage: python logmon.py sample.cfg

